==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: erysipeloid
<hw>er`y*sip"e*loid</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧r`⟦icr⟧*s⟦icr⟧p"⟦esl⟧*loid)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., fr. Gr. <grk>'erysi`pelas</grk>;
<grk>'eryqro`s</grk> red + <grk>pe`lla</grk> hide, skin. See
<er>Red</er>, and <er>Pell</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>a usually self-limiting cellulitis of the hand somewhat resembling
erysipelas, caused by the bacterium <spn>Erysipelothrix
rhusiopathiae</spn>. It may start at the site of a wound obtained while
handling meat or fish, and may occasionally become generalized with
protracted illness and severe toxemia.</def> <au>Stedman</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erysipelothrix</ent>⟦br⟧
